title: Pratarak
subTitle: A young man leaves his wealthy father to work in the city without knowing of a conspiracy by a trusted manager to take over his parent's business.

title: Taan
subTitle: When a photographer goes missing in the Sundarbans, his friend, Lisa, goes to look for him. Her journey brings her face-to-face with the women in the region who are forced into prostitution.

title: Shiv Shakti
subTitle: Parvati agrees to marry as she gives the utmost importance to her parents' wishes. However, Narada Muni is determined to change Parvati's decision.

title: Aagoon
subTitle: A childless couple adopts an orphan whose parents died under mysterious circumstances. Eventually, the orphan grows up and embarks on a quest to uncover the truth behind his parents' suspicious death.

title: SWAMIR ADESH
subTitle: Sunil, an honest judge, abandons his pregnant wife due to a misunderstanding created by his aunt. However, years later, he fights a case in his daughter's favour and reunites with his family.

title: Streer Maryada
subTitle: Saptami, an orphan, marries a rich doctor who spends most of his time at work. A few days into the marriage, her in-laws start harassing her but things go awry when they humiliate her brother.

title: Minister Phatakesto
subTitle: Fatakeshto, an MLA turned home minister, vows to rescue the government from a massive financial loss while political thugs create several hurdles for him.

title: Jiban Niye Khela
subTitle: In the distant village of Dharampur, Dr Subhankar Sanyal fights the bureaucracy and brings justice to the lives of his patients.

title: Wanted
subTitle: The police kill Shibu, an innocent man, after mistaking him to be his lookalike Raja, an assassin. To escape from the police, Raja starts living with Shibu's parents as their son.

title: Bornoporichoy
subTitle: Dhananjoy, a police detective, goes on a desperate lookout for Arko, a man who murders people, taking inspiration from the five elements- Earth, Water, Wind, Sky, and Fire.

title: Bornoporichoy
subTitle: Dhananjoy, a police detective, goes on a desperate lookout for Arko, a man who murders people, taking inspiration from the five elements- Earth, Water, Wind, Sky, and Fire.

title: Ek Je Chhilo Raja
subTitle: A prince dies of illness while he is abroad for treatment, causing grief throughout his estate. Decades later, a religious physician claims to be the resurrected heir.

title: Shiv Shakti
subTitle: After Goddess Parvati reveals her wish to be devoted to Lord Shiva, she worships the Shiva linga as water falls on Lord Shiva.

title: Shatru Dhangso
subTitle: A dedicated ranger risks everything to dimantle a smuggling network, battling dangerous criminals and corrupt officials while trying to protect his forest and his integrity.

title: Gharer Laxmi
subTitle: Poor bride faces wealthy father-in-law's wrath after he cruelly tries to separate his son from his wife and child, but fate intervenes.

title: Dujone
subTitle: Akash is the son of a rich industrialist who falls in love with a poor girl and intends to marry her. Soon, their families find out and start opposing their relationship.

title: Annadata
subTitle: Sankar's life changes when he gets taken in by a rich businessman. Years later, an opportunity arises for him to prove his loyalty to his adopted family.

title: Hirak Jayanti
subTitle: Though they initially quarrel, Jaya and Hiru eventually fall in love with each other. Problems arise after Jaya's father feels that the uneducated Hiru is not good enough for his daughter.

title: MLA Phatakesto
subTitle: A notorious goon aspires to become a member of the Legislative Assembly and in an attempt to do so, he gives himself seven days.

title: Khiladi
subTitle: Two families of opposing faiths are in a long-standing rivalry over land and past wounds. However, one man vows to reunite them by disguising himself as a Hindu person.

title: Khiladi
subTitle: Two families of opposing faiths are in a long-standing rivalry over land and past wounds. However, one man vows to reunite them by disguising himself as a Hindu person.

title: Krishna
subTitle: Krishna and his friends are in grave trouble when they are accosted by a furious father who believes them to have helped his elder daughter elope.

title: Shiv Shakti
subTitle: With folded hands, Parvati pleads before Shiva to accept her solemn prayers, eventually taking a pledge to construct a huge Shiva linga.

title: Gumnaami
subTitle: In contradiction to previous claims, a journalist comes up with a theory revolving around the mysterious existence and death of Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose as Gumnaami Baba.

title: Ami Subhash Bolchi
subTitle: Debabrata Bose, a conflicted man, awakens the spirit of late Bengali patriot Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose as he fights for change and strives to unite his Bengali community.

title: Dui Prithibi
subTitle: A rich man falls in love with an idealistic medical student. However, when circumstances force them apart, he learns the true meaning and value of love.

title: Poran Jaye Jolia Re
subTitle: A young man, Rabin, meets three different women at different stages in his life. The relationship he shares with these women, though very different from each other, help him grow as a person.

title: Prem Amar
subTitle: A young man falls in love with his new neighbour. However, his life takes a turn for the worse when he learns that she is betrothed to another man.

title: Fighter, Marbo Noy Morbo
subTitle: Surya, a college student, decides to exact revenge on a local gangster after he frames and kills his elder brother, ACP Bose.

title: Mon Mane Na
subTitle: On their way to Siliguri, India, Rahul and Ria bump into each other. While Rahul plans to sell a stolen necklace, Ria is excited to meet her boyfriend.
